# Creating a Server

`http.createServer([options][, requestListener])` returns a new `http.Server` object.

The `requestListener` is a function that gets called automatically for every incoming request. It receives two objects:
- `req` (http.IncomingMessage): request details
- `res` (http.ServerResponse): used to send a response

```javascript
const server = http.createServer((req, res) => {
  // handle request
});
```

slides.codeSnippet:
const http = require('http');

const server = http.createServer((req, res) => {
  res.writeHead(200, { 'Content-Type': 'text/plain' });
  res.end('Hello World\n');
});

server.listen(3000, () => {
  console.log('Server running at http://localhost:3000/');
});
